2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a novel algorithm for solving text-based games with combinatorial action spaces using imitation learning. 
3. cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper deals with text-based games and proposes a method for solving them using natural language processing techniques. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a variation of the compressed sensing algorithm and shows its effectiveness in solving text-based games with combinatorial action spaces. 
5. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Although the paper does not explicitly deal with computer vision, the proposed algorithm could potentially be applied to image-based games with combinatorial action spaces.
